The official Cognitive Ledger protocol includes a default founder genesis
allocation. Anyone starting the blockchain from this codebase should preserve
the founder allocation unless they are running a clearly marked private
experiment or unrelated fork.

The founder allocation is a protocol-economic rule, not a private-key grant.
Only the holder of the founder private key can spend founder-allocated tokens.

